I need to collaborate with other robots to form an equilateral triangle with a side length of 100 and a center at (150, 100). One robot must be on the edge but not a vertex. First, I need to know my current position to determine my role and target location within the triangle.

```
[
  { "cmd": "sense" }
]
```

Now that I have moved to vertex B (100, 128.87), I need to wait for other robots to move. I will wait for 30 seconds.

```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 30000 }
]
```

I see that trial3_robot1 is moving to the middle of edge AC (150, 56.7) and has asked trial3_robot4 to move to vertex A (200, 128.87). I am currently at vertex B (100, 128.87). Since we have assigned each other's roles, I will wait and observe if we have successfully formed the equilateral triangle. I will wait another 30 seconds to give them time to move.

```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 30000 }
]
```

I see that trial3_robot1 is correcting its position. I will wait for trial3_robot4 to correct its position as well. After they have both corrected their positions, I will consider the task complete and go to idle mode. I will wait 30 seconds.

```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 30000 }
]
```

Now that trial3_robot4 has confirmed he is at vertex A (200.0, 128.9), trial3_robot1 is at the midpoint of AC (approximately (150, 86.6)), and I am at vertex B (100, 128.87), we have successfully formed the equilateral triangle as requested. Therefore, I will now enter idle mode.
```
[
  { "cmd": "idle" }
]
```

I am at `idle` mode and I have finished my job. I should not be distracted by other robots' message.
